-- W7/W9: an out-of-bounds Array index.  Since #16b the bound check lives in the
-- prelude's `impl Index (Array a) Int a`, which raises the coded `indexError`
-- (E-INDEX-OOB) — so this needs the real prelude (MODULES corpus).  Both the native
-- oracle and the WasmGC module abort with EMPTY stdout, the SAME coded
-- `runtime error [E-INDEX-OOB]: index out of bounds` stderr line, and exit 1 — since
-- #531 diff_wasm_modules.sh compares stderr and exit code too (not just stdout), so
-- this is a genuine assertion that both engines trap identically, not just a
-- stdout-blind "empty == empty".
main = [|5, 6, 7|].[9]
